title: Case Studies in Indigenous Venture Creation
description: A study of approximately a dozen cases of ventures created by Indigenous entrepreneurs. The cases will reflect a variety of sectors and will be drawn from a variety of regions.

title: Practicum in Indigenous Entrepreneurship 2
description: The instructor works with each student to identify a real world experience in the field of Indigenous entrepreneurship and to plan how they will use that experience to achieve an agreed-upon set of learning outcomes. The instructor provides mentorship and coaching as each student works through the course they have created for themselves.
